WEBVTT

00:01.535 --> 00:03.118
-[micah]<i> previously on</i>
queen sugar...
-[knocks on door]

00:03.204 --> 00:05.320
[celine]<i> I'm just afraid</i>
<i> that he's gonna be</i>
<i> able to track us down here.</i>

00:05.406 --> 00:06.822
I've been where you've been.

00:06.907 --> 00:09.375
We're not gonna be
able to hide away
in a cabana.

00:09.493 --> 00:11.744
Then maybe it's time
we tell the family.

00:11.846 --> 00:13.328
I'm billie denton,
prosper's daughter.

00:13.414 --> 00:15.214
[violet]<i> she says</i>
<i> that I can't visit prosper.</i>

00:15.332 --> 00:17.416
Not at the hospital
or at the house.

00:17.501 --> 00:19.418
[nova]<i> look, we may not be</i>
<i> prosper's blood,</i>

00:19.503 --> 00:20.969
but we are family.

00:21.055 --> 00:22.054
And you owe me.

00:22.156 --> 00:23.989
You are having a little girl.

00:24.091 --> 00:25.324
Yeah.

00:25.426 --> 00:27.760
You're gonna
love your baby girl
better than I loved mine.

00:27.862 --> 00:29.928
[ralph]<i> it ain't over</i>
<i> till it's over, mr. Prosper.</i>

00:32.600 --> 00:34.016
-[man] oh.
-[charley] hey, hey.

00:34.101 --> 00:36.151
[cheers and applause]

00:36.237 --> 00:39.271
I can do it, it's just
making too much fuss.

00:39.356 --> 00:41.857
[billie] a few more weeks
of physical therapy
and you'll be good as new.

00:41.942 --> 00:43.525
[hollywood] no,
better than new.

00:43.611 --> 00:45.994
Gonna have to put up
a fist to keep
the ladies away, right?

00:46.080 --> 00:48.997
You gave us quite a scare,
prosper.

00:49.083 --> 00:50.949
[hollywood] ah, that's just
the first round.

00:51.035 --> 00:53.118
He'll come back like ali, huh?

00:53.220 --> 00:54.753
[charley] you look good.

00:54.855 --> 00:56.021
Mmm.

00:56.123 --> 00:57.589
[violet] welcome, baby.

00:58.209 --> 00:59.792
Can I get you anything?

00:59.877 --> 01:01.260
[prosper] no, I'm fine.

01:02.596 --> 01:05.130
Unless you got
some of that pecan pie
with you.

01:05.216 --> 01:07.516
[laughs]

01:07.601 --> 01:11.186
I told hollywood that
you were gonna want some.

01:11.272 --> 01:13.522
I got you.

01:13.607 --> 01:16.775
Yeah, you know,
I wish I could see
your face behind that mask.

01:16.894 --> 01:19.561
I can feel the love, though.
Yeah, thank you.

01:20.114 --> 01:21.480
[chuckles]

01:31.759 --> 01:33.158
[nova] hey.

01:35.079 --> 01:36.378
[prosper] how are you?

01:36.464 --> 01:38.997
This can't be easy
for either of you,

01:39.083 --> 01:41.333
stepping into these new roles.

01:41.418 --> 01:43.552
He's so open with your family.

01:43.637 --> 01:45.704
[charley] just give it
some time.

01:45.806 --> 01:48.640
When you're in chicago,
all he talks about is you.

01:48.759 --> 01:52.678
And when I'm here,
all he talks about
is the bordelons.

01:52.763 --> 01:55.597
[charley] then there's love
on both sides
of the equation.

01:58.602 --> 02:01.753
Just think about this
as a do-over,

02:01.856 --> 02:05.491
you know, a chance to make it
what you want it to be.

02:08.129 --> 02:09.912
[billie sighs]

02:09.997 --> 02:12.114
[nova] I'm so glad to see you
out of that hospital.

02:12.199 --> 02:13.282
[prosper] yeah. Me, too.

02:13.367 --> 02:15.701
Yeah, counting my blessings.

02:15.786 --> 02:19.121
Keep thinking
about all those people
that couldn't come home.

02:19.790 --> 02:22.490
Amen.
Too much pain this year.

02:23.344 --> 02:25.794
But you waking up
was a ray of light.

02:27.298 --> 02:30.048
Keep shining on us, okay?

02:30.134 --> 02:32.768
I intend to.
You know, I intend to.

02:32.853 --> 02:33.886
[laughs]

02:36.807 --> 02:40.726
<i> ♪ dreams never die,</i>
<i> take flight</i>
<i> as the world turns ♪</i>

02:40.811 --> 02:44.396
<i> ♪ dreams never die,</i>
<i> take flight</i>
<i> as the world turns ♪</i>

02:44.481 --> 02:47.199
<i> ♪ keep the colors</i>
<i> in the lines, take flight ♪</i>

02:48.819 --> 02:50.536
<i> ♪ dreams never die ♪</i>

02:56.377 --> 03:00.245
<i> ♪ keep the colors</i>
<i> in the lines ♪</i>

03:00.331 --> 03:02.998
<i> ♪ keep the colors</i>
<i> in the lines, take flight ♪</i>

03:07.504 --> 03:08.670
[hollywood laughs]

03:11.091 --> 03:12.307
-[hollywood] yeah.
-[violet] ooh.

03:12.393 --> 03:13.759
[violet laughs]

03:13.844 --> 03:15.260
-[hollywood] oh, baby.
-[violet] hey, baby.

03:15.346 --> 03:16.929
[hollywood] oh, is this all
for my grand opening?

03:17.014 --> 03:18.730
We're gonna need
more napkins for the ribs.

03:18.849 --> 03:22.351
No, sir. Your supplies are
already boxed up in the back.

03:22.436 --> 03:24.069
What's this big, old box?
Who is it for?

03:24.171 --> 03:27.105
My customers.
Stop being so nosy.

03:27.191 --> 03:29.274
You need to mind
your own business.

03:29.360 --> 03:32.277
Hey, can you
pick up the rentals?

03:32.363 --> 03:34.279
They're reserved
under the real spot.

03:34.365 --> 03:35.747
I'm on it.

03:35.866 --> 03:37.032
I'm on it, I'm on it.

03:43.591 --> 03:45.040
[bills rustling]

03:56.637 --> 03:58.887
you sure? How low?

03:58.973 --> 04:00.355
[woman]<i> really low.</i>

04:00.441 --> 04:02.975
So basically
you're saying both
cane hauls is a bust?

04:03.060 --> 04:04.610
<i> -Yeah.</i>
-Damn.

04:06.146 --> 04:07.696
All right.

04:07.781 --> 04:10.032
If you could salvage anything,
I appreciate it.

04:10.117 --> 04:11.617
<i> Will do.</i>

04:11.735 --> 04:12.918
-[man] see you in a minute.
-[charley] yep.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.121
You okay, ralph?

04:16.240 --> 04:18.290
What's up with
them arbitrations?

04:18.409 --> 04:19.358
Some of us
ain't gonna make it

04:19.460 --> 04:21.243
if those remedy checks
don't come in soon.

04:21.328 --> 04:23.495
Look,
if you need anything, I--

04:23.580 --> 04:25.497
-you know, right?
-It's a little deeper
than that, charley.

04:25.582 --> 04:27.799
We wouldn't be in this mess
without the usda.

04:28.736 --> 04:30.002
They need to pay up.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.472
[charley] hopefully we'll get
some answers today.

04:33.574 --> 04:34.973
-Oh, hi.
-[nova] hey.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.092
-What up, there?
-Hi.

04:37.177 --> 04:38.176
-[man] hey.
-[ralph] what's up?

04:38.279 --> 04:39.845
-[billie] hi.
-[charley] hi.

04:39.930 --> 04:41.213
[billie] hi.

04:41.315 --> 04:43.682
Prosper asked her
to stand in for him.

04:43.767 --> 04:46.518
You know,
she be doing her little
real-estate thing in chicago.

04:46.603 --> 04:47.919
Well,
I'm just a paralegal,

04:48.022 --> 04:50.222
but I've been helping with
redlining cases for years.

04:50.324 --> 04:52.891
It's all legal
mumbo-jumbo to me.

04:52.993 --> 04:55.494
Good to have somebody
who speak their language
on our side.

04:55.612 --> 04:57.496
I just want
my daddy's paperwork
to be right.

04:57.614 --> 05:00.132
And if I can help
anyone along the way,
I'm happy to do so.

05:02.102 --> 05:03.201
I'll see you inside.

05:03.320 --> 05:05.454
-Nova.
-[nova] afternoon.

05:07.291 --> 05:08.623
Don't let her fool you.

05:08.709 --> 05:10.459
She talks a good game,
but you can't trust her.

05:10.544 --> 05:13.295
What I'm not gonna do is
get between y'all little beef.

05:13.380 --> 05:14.663
Come on.

05:21.839 --> 05:23.221
[charley] sheriff,

05:23.841 --> 05:25.007
can I help you?

05:25.793 --> 05:26.842
No, ma'am.

05:27.845 --> 05:29.811
Let me be more specific.

05:29.897 --> 05:31.263
What are you doing here?

05:31.348 --> 05:33.815
Oh, we got a call
from a concerned citizen.

05:33.901 --> 05:34.900
[nova] about what?

05:35.019 --> 05:36.651
It's a meeting
for the farmers collective.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.487
The black farmers collective.

05:38.572 --> 05:40.439
[ralph] you're saying
black folk can't
have a meeting?

05:40.541 --> 05:42.324
What are you saying,
I can't attend
a public meeting

05:42.409 --> 05:44.042
paid for by my tax dollars?

05:46.030 --> 05:47.379
Of course you can.

05:51.035 --> 05:52.484
Of course I can.

05:55.339 --> 05:56.588
[ralph] what is this, charley?

05:57.541 --> 05:58.924
Feel like a setup.

06:00.844 --> 06:02.160
[door closes]

06:11.739 --> 06:13.205
[keys rattling]

06:16.543 --> 06:18.110
you want to tell me
what's going on?

06:24.568 --> 06:26.084
[siren wailing in distance]

06:29.256 --> 06:30.505
[knocks on door]

06:35.596 --> 06:37.429
hey, celine.
It's okay.

06:38.265 --> 06:41.433
He knows.
This is hollywood, my husband.

06:41.518 --> 06:43.351
He wanted to meet you.

06:43.437 --> 06:45.136
Nice to meet you,
mr. Hollywood.

06:45.239 --> 06:48.156
-[hollywood] and who is this?
-Come on.

06:48.275 --> 06:53.144
This is my son gabriel,
named after the angel
from the bible.

06:53.247 --> 06:55.430
Are you famous, mr. Hollywood?

06:55.532 --> 06:58.533
I'm famous at tic-tac-toe.
You know what that is?

06:58.786 --> 06:59.984
No, sir.

07:00.087 --> 07:01.586
Oh, we gonna have to fix that.

07:08.962 --> 07:10.345
[chuckles]

07:10.447 --> 07:14.099
that is the first time
I've seen my baby smile
in weeks.

07:15.636 --> 07:18.019
I sure can't seem
to make him smile anymore.

07:18.138 --> 07:21.673
He will smile again
when you can smile again.

07:21.775 --> 07:24.126
You've got a lot
on your shoulders, baby.

07:24.228 --> 07:26.194
But you're surviving.

07:26.313 --> 07:29.481
Ma'am, I feel like
I've been barely surviving now
for over a year.

07:30.284 --> 07:33.068
It just won't let up.

07:33.170 --> 07:35.487
We was all trapped
in that house

07:35.572 --> 07:38.206
when greg lost his job
because of covid,

07:38.325 --> 07:42.744
no work for either of us,
no school for gabriel.

07:42.830 --> 07:47.532
I thought, "that man
has been taken
his frustrations out on me

07:47.634 --> 07:49.000
since we got married.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.803
I'm getting used to it."

07:52.840 --> 07:54.506
but then,

07:54.591 --> 07:57.676
them little pops in the mouth
turned into fists in my face.

07:59.096 --> 08:01.346
I felt my soul
slipping away.

08:02.015 --> 08:03.181
I thought I could take it.

08:03.267 --> 08:05.600
I've been taking it
all these years but...

08:07.821 --> 08:09.437
Ooh, ms. Vi,

08:09.523 --> 08:13.992
the man started taking
his frustrations out
on gabriel

08:14.828 --> 08:16.227
and I had to go.

08:16.864 --> 08:19.948
Nobody is hurting my baby.

08:21.518 --> 08:22.868
[violet] you're right.

08:22.953 --> 08:26.955
Nobody's hurting your baby
and nobody's hurting you,
not anymore.

08:28.375 --> 08:32.744
That's all because
you took a stand for yourself.

08:32.829 --> 08:34.796
You got out of there.

08:34.882 --> 08:40.719
You're smart.
You came to a parish
where he don't know folks.

08:41.522 --> 08:43.254
And, baby,

08:43.357 --> 08:46.224
you connected
with the right people, baby.

08:46.894 --> 08:50.562
You are here, you are safe.

08:51.481 --> 08:53.932
And you are going
to get through this

08:54.034 --> 08:57.285
and have
a beautiful testimony.

08:57.404 --> 08:58.987
Believe that.

09:01.742 --> 09:03.258
[violet laughs]

09:08.048 --> 09:09.965
[indistinct conversations]

09:10.083 --> 09:12.784
[representative] look,
I understand your frustration

09:12.886 --> 09:14.669
and I'll get
to all of your questions.

09:15.756 --> 09:18.089
There's only one question
that matters.

09:18.175 --> 09:20.425
When y'all gonna make
receipts for our claims

09:20.510 --> 09:22.510
-and when y'all gonna
cut our checks?
-[man] that's right.

09:22.596 --> 09:25.146
-We have to take
every allegation seriously.
-[ralph] mm-hmm.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.982
And that's caused
some unexpected delays.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.817
[ralph] now we've been jacked
around long enough,

09:28.919 --> 09:30.101
-y'all need to pay us.
-[all] pay us.

09:30.187 --> 09:32.787
Pay us! Pay us! Pay us!

09:32.889 --> 09:36.524
First, you got
to be black to get a vaccine
and now this?

09:36.627 --> 09:38.159
Where's our special fund?

09:38.262 --> 09:40.278
[charley] okay,
this fund was set up

09:40.364 --> 09:42.697
to cover
generational discrimination.

09:42.783 --> 09:45.283
Seems like
it's about reparations to me.

09:45.369 --> 09:46.818
[nova] this isn't reparations.

09:46.920 --> 09:50.005
Reparations will be
paying back the $5.9 trillion

09:50.123 --> 09:52.123
owed to our ancestors
and their descendants.

09:52.209 --> 09:54.175
-See, she admits it,
right out of her mouth.
-[nova] oh, yeah, thief.

09:54.294 --> 09:56.878
You stole proceedings
from our vaccine drive!

09:56.964 --> 09:58.346
You're stealing right now.

09:58.465 --> 10:02.017
We're processing these claims
as fast as we can.

10:02.135 --> 10:04.552
But the more claims,
the slower the process.

10:04.638 --> 10:08.023
All claims have
to be fully investigated.

10:08.141 --> 10:10.809
It can take time,
longer than you might expect.

10:12.279 --> 10:15.680
[billie] sir,
<i> pigford v. Glickman</i> already
set the legal precedent.

10:15.782 --> 10:17.699
The patterns of discrimination
are clear.

10:17.818 --> 10:19.534
There's no point
in dragging this out.

10:19.653 --> 10:21.736
Pay these farmers
what they are owed

10:21.822 --> 10:24.406
or they'll be forced
to take their grievances
to court for emergency relief.

10:24.491 --> 10:25.790
[applause]

10:30.964 --> 10:32.213
[representative]
that's the update we have.

10:32.332 --> 10:33.581
We'll have another
in about six weeks.

10:33.684 --> 10:34.983
-[man] six weeks?
-[woman] six weeks?

10:35.085 --> 10:36.418
[ralph] what do you mean
six weeks, huh?

10:36.520 --> 10:38.920
What am I supposed to do
for six weeks? Hey!

10:39.022 --> 10:40.588
Six weeks!

10:40.674 --> 10:42.173
[indistinct conversations]

10:46.680 --> 10:48.013
why you ain't tell me, vi?

10:49.182 --> 10:52.067
Now what if...
What if her husband showed up?

10:52.185 --> 10:53.518
And I ain't even know
where you were.

10:54.688 --> 10:56.071
This is what I'm always
talking about, vi.

10:56.189 --> 10:58.356
And that's why
I didn't tell you.

10:59.660 --> 11:02.393
'cause I knew this is exactly
how you would act,

11:02.496 --> 11:06.898
telling me that I'm always
helping everybody else.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.367
I just didn't want
to fight anymore
about how I do me.

11:09.453 --> 11:12.087
That's what
you think about me,
just a broken record.

11:12.205 --> 11:15.623
Look, you and me,
we're the same.

11:15.709 --> 11:20.378
The real spot is just you
taking care of everybody else
instead of yourself.

11:22.849 --> 11:23.882
Wow.

11:31.975 --> 11:33.641
[sighs]

11:33.727 --> 11:35.226
[car door closes]

11:46.957 --> 11:48.656
[cell phone ringing]

11:54.831 --> 11:56.214
[can clinks]

11:56.299 --> 11:58.449
-yeah, what?
-[charley]<i> yeah, what?</i>

11:58.552 --> 12:01.970
[scoffs]<i> I know</i>
<i> I raised you better than</i>
<i>to answer the phone like that.</i>

12:02.089 --> 12:04.089
[micah]<i> sorry,</i>
<i> I didn't see it was you.</i>

12:04.174 --> 12:06.424
I just want to remind you
about dinner tonight

12:06.510 --> 12:09.460
with your dad
and the family at aunt vi's.

12:09.563 --> 12:12.013
That's a sentence
I never thought
I'd hear you say again.

12:16.603 --> 12:19.187
Well, um,
do you want to talk about it,

12:19.740 --> 12:20.939
talk it through?

12:23.610 --> 12:26.861
Your feelings about
all of this are important
to us, micah.

12:27.748 --> 12:29.147
I hope you know that.

12:29.249 --> 12:30.982
<i> No, no.</i>

12:31.084 --> 12:34.586
I just want you to be happy.

12:34.671 --> 12:35.754
<i> I want him to be happy.</i>

12:35.839 --> 12:38.006
So if you two think that
you can be happy together,

12:38.108 --> 12:40.208
then, by all means,
go for it.

12:42.112 --> 12:43.411
All right? Um,

12:44.714 --> 12:46.748
I don't want you
to hurt like that again.

12:48.051 --> 12:49.634
<i> I don't think</i>
<i> either of us could take it.</i>

12:51.104 --> 12:53.104
Thank you, baby, for...
For saying that.

12:54.391 --> 12:55.356
I hear you.

12:55.475 --> 12:57.358
I'll, um,
I'll see you later tonight?

12:57.461 --> 12:58.626
I'll see you tonight.

12:58.728 --> 12:59.861
Bye, sweetheart.

13:01.648 --> 13:04.149
Guess I thought
he'd be happier

13:04.234 --> 13:05.567
that we were back together.

13:08.104 --> 13:10.655
He used to talk about it
all the time.

13:10.740 --> 13:12.874
He won't be alone
in his reservations.

13:14.327 --> 13:16.027
[inhales sharply]

13:16.129 --> 13:19.831
you know, some of your family
might not be too happy
seeing us together.

13:21.334 --> 13:23.334
And no one in your family
is gonna hold back.

13:23.420 --> 13:27.388
Well, I know
some might be surprised,

13:27.507 --> 13:30.541
but I don't think anyone
is gonna be opposed.

13:30.644 --> 13:31.976
Well,

13:32.062 --> 13:35.480
I am ready to plead my case
with the court
of the bordelons.

13:35.565 --> 13:36.731
[chuckles]

13:36.850 --> 13:39.234
-I have my opening remarks
ready, my rebuttals.
-Wow.

13:39.352 --> 13:42.904
Yeah, and I just have
to withstand
the cross-examination

13:43.023 --> 13:45.156
so that I can get
to my closing argument.

13:45.242 --> 13:46.774
They are indeed a handful.

13:48.528 --> 13:51.412
May not be easy,
but you're up to it.

13:51.531 --> 13:52.997
Ain't no other way to be.

14:00.457 --> 14:01.873
[door closes]

14:03.510 --> 14:05.376
[kids chattering]

14:11.134 --> 14:13.601
[woman] I saw your talk
with tarana burke
on your live.

14:13.720 --> 14:15.220
It was powerful.

14:15.305 --> 14:18.056
Thank you.
Thanks very much.

14:18.141 --> 14:19.691
-Did you watch?
-Of course I did.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.776
Excellent, as always.

14:21.895 --> 14:24.262
You got me thinking about
our intersection
with whiteness.

14:24.364 --> 14:28.700
It's a lot to unpack.
A lot to process.

14:29.736 --> 14:32.270
What, am I being too dramatic?

14:32.372 --> 14:34.205
No, you should just check out
my uncle's new space

14:34.291 --> 14:35.957
the real spot
one of these days.

14:36.076 --> 14:37.709
It's a place
for men to process.

14:37.794 --> 14:39.460
I'm not sure
what goes on in there,

14:39.563 --> 14:42.046
but maybe you can
give us ladies a scoop on
what happens inside.

14:42.132 --> 14:43.965
[woman] yeah,
we want the scoop.

14:44.084 --> 14:45.133
Oh, no, ma'am.
No, ma'am.

14:45.252 --> 14:46.901
If the real spot
is a spot just for men,

14:47.003 --> 14:49.804
then what happens
at the real spot stays
at the real spot.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.806
Oh, you got slogans.

14:51.925 --> 14:54.058
I've been writing them down.

14:54.144 --> 14:55.476
Bye, y'all.

15:11.528 --> 15:12.777
[gate rattles]

15:13.780 --> 15:15.663
[party music playing]

15:19.869 --> 15:22.787
