32:04.115 --> 32:05.414
Oh.

32:05.500 --> 32:08.784
Okay, well,
could you give him this
and tell him I came by?

32:08.870 --> 32:10.035
Sure.

32:14.125 --> 32:16.625
You know it's childish that
we don't talk about things.

32:19.130 --> 32:20.713
How would you like to start?

32:20.798 --> 32:22.298
You could try an apology.

32:25.553 --> 32:27.019
We were kids.

32:27.138 --> 32:28.554
It was an accident.

32:28.639 --> 32:29.939
An accident?

32:30.024 --> 32:32.391
What you said
to my father damaged
my relationship with him

32:32.476 --> 32:33.792
for the rest of his life.

32:36.147 --> 32:37.613
He never looked
at me the same.

32:37.698 --> 32:40.449
We were 18,
we both did things back then.

32:40.535 --> 32:42.368
No, you don't get
to get off that easy.

32:42.470 --> 32:44.537
You knew exactly
what you were doing,
that's what made it worse.

32:44.639 --> 32:46.655
You did it on purpose.

32:46.741 --> 32:48.490
Nova, I don't remember
all the details.

32:48.576 --> 32:51.126
All I remember is that
I was hurting.

32:51.212 --> 32:52.661
And you hurt me, too.

32:54.332 --> 32:58.083
You told my father
you were worried about my soul
because I might be gay.

33:00.004 --> 33:01.554
You outed me, billie.

33:04.008 --> 33:07.142
I came home to questions
I wasn't prepared to answer,

33:07.228 --> 33:09.011
for me or for myself.

33:09.096 --> 33:11.897
And for you to sit here
and say that
it happened accidentally

33:13.067 --> 33:14.233
is vile.

33:15.186 --> 33:16.902
Vile?

33:17.021 --> 33:18.520
No, I'll tell you what's vile.

33:20.074 --> 33:22.691
Abandoning your best friend
when she needed you the most.

33:22.777 --> 33:24.159
When did I abandon you,
billie?

33:24.245 --> 33:25.494
Me and jimmy dale.

33:25.580 --> 33:26.679
Oh, so the rumor is true.

33:26.781 --> 33:27.863
Ah, you...

33:28.950 --> 33:31.750
You are so high
and mighty on tv

33:31.869 --> 33:33.535
and in your books
and in your articles,

33:33.621 --> 33:36.755
crusading for justice
and women's rights,

33:38.626 --> 33:40.676
but you couldn't see
then or now

33:40.761 --> 33:42.211
what is really happening.

33:44.265 --> 33:48.133
I was 18 years old, nova.

33:48.219 --> 33:51.770
He was over 33.
There was no me
and jimmy dale.

33:51.872 --> 33:54.773
There was a
30-something-year-old man
going around town

33:54.892 --> 33:57.860
telling people
that an 18-year-old senior
in high school

33:57.945 --> 33:59.278
was good in bed.

34:00.615 --> 34:02.114
And not one of you,

34:03.567 --> 34:07.486
not my best friend,
or anyone in her family

34:07.571 --> 34:10.406
thought to inquire
about the circumstances.

34:10.491 --> 34:12.207
What are you saying, billie?

34:12.293 --> 34:13.659
I'm saying

34:14.428 --> 34:17.796
the same thing that
I wanted to tell you then.

34:18.633 --> 34:22.584
I tried to tell violet
and my father

34:23.170 --> 34:24.837
and everybody back then.

34:28.009 --> 34:29.475
It wasn't my choice.

34:32.647 --> 34:34.096
But nobody would listen.

34:35.650 --> 34:37.599
[crying] nobody.

34:37.685 --> 34:40.586
So, as soon as
I graduated, I left.

34:42.106 --> 34:44.823
And on my way out,
I stepped by the farm

34:44.942 --> 34:47.359
to speak with your father
to see if he would listen.

34:48.829 --> 34:50.195
And he did.

34:51.198 --> 34:53.949
And he was so kind, nova.

34:56.120 --> 34:57.953
I think he might have
even believed me.

35:00.341 --> 35:01.623
I saw in him

35:02.460 --> 35:03.625
a good person.

35:05.463 --> 35:07.012
A father who listened,

35:09.633 --> 35:11.183
and mine didn't,

35:12.853 --> 35:16.138
and that made me so, so sad,

35:17.224 --> 35:18.724
and mad.

35:20.194 --> 35:22.478
And I didn't want you to have
what I didn't have.

35:24.899 --> 35:26.865
So I told him you liked girls.

35:31.322 --> 35:33.489
Just to fight back
what was happening to me.

35:35.910 --> 35:38.327
I left this town
and I never looked back.

35:44.001 --> 35:45.000
[door slams]

35:50.007 --> 35:53.008
to you,
for picking up the pieces,

35:54.061 --> 35:57.730
making amends,
humbling yourself,

35:57.848 --> 36:00.933
studying, networking,

36:01.018 --> 36:05.771
stepping out on faith,
and nailing the job,

36:05.856 --> 36:09.408
mr. New head coach
of the los angeles dynasty.

36:09.527 --> 36:11.527
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

36:11.612 --> 36:13.695
And to you,

36:15.866 --> 36:18.367
for not letting
my mistakes take you down,

36:19.754 --> 36:21.420
for rising above the mess,

36:21.539 --> 36:24.757
for coming here
and helping your family,

36:25.376 --> 36:27.259
finding a greater cause,

36:27.378 --> 36:31.547
for running
and winning an election,

36:31.632 --> 36:33.465
and grabbing the attention
of the party.

36:33.551 --> 36:37.970
Baby,
you are the hottest emerging
black woman political figure

36:38.055 --> 36:39.972
in the country right now.

36:41.392 --> 36:43.525
-The sky's the limit.
-For both of us.

36:43.611 --> 36:45.110
-Mm-hmm.
-[glasses clink]

36:49.733 --> 36:51.150
[davis] mmm.

36:53.237 --> 36:54.319
Wow.

36:54.405 --> 36:56.071
-Hmm.
-[davis sighs]

36:59.743 --> 37:02.244
-you don't get stars
like this everywhere.
-Mmm.

37:02.329 --> 37:03.712
This is something special

37:03.798 --> 37:05.964
I only see in places
where there's no smog,

37:06.083 --> 37:07.666
-or city lights.
-Hmm.

37:11.422 --> 37:13.305
Would you give
this all up for politics?

37:15.810 --> 37:17.759
I'm not giving up
anything anymore.

37:20.014 --> 37:22.264
-I want it all.
-Mm-hmm.

37:24.602 --> 37:26.485
See, that's what I love
about you.

37:27.188 --> 37:29.104
Fearlessness.

37:29.190 --> 37:30.856
I got to admit,
I'm a little scared about

37:30.941 --> 37:34.409
what the feedback will be once
my announcement goes up.

37:34.495 --> 37:37.746
I hate that it's something
you got to think about
while dealing with the party.

37:37.832 --> 37:41.667
We'll get out ahead of it
and control
what they're saying.

37:41.785 --> 37:45.170
The party,
the sports press will think
what we want them to think.

37:45.623 --> 37:46.955
Remember,

37:47.791 --> 37:51.126
we set the tone and this,

37:51.795 --> 37:53.295
us,

37:54.298 --> 37:55.797
we're a feel-good story.

37:56.967 --> 37:58.667
Golden couple

37:59.470 --> 38:01.386
who lost themselves
in the fame,

38:02.139 --> 38:04.022
separated,

38:04.141 --> 38:06.275
found themselves separately,

38:06.360 --> 38:09.311
and reunited
to be stronger than ever.

38:09.864 --> 38:11.313
[chuckles]

38:12.149 --> 38:13.982
I swear, charley, you...

38:15.319 --> 38:17.653
You have such a gift
with this kind of stuff

38:17.738 --> 38:19.321
'cause you make
it sound so easy.

38:22.209 --> 38:24.243
But I don't want
to lean on you,

38:24.328 --> 38:26.545
to rehabilitate my image.

38:26.664 --> 38:27.829
I don't even want an image.

38:28.999 --> 38:31.633
I just want to go
about my work quietly,

38:31.719 --> 38:33.502
contribute to a good team,

38:34.672 --> 38:36.505
enjoy the games,
and come home to you.

38:38.559 --> 38:39.841
I don't need the other stuff.

38:41.595 --> 38:43.395
I want people to see you

38:44.348 --> 38:45.764
the way I see you.

38:52.406 --> 38:54.439
I only care how you see me.

38:54.525 --> 38:55.908
I want you to be proud of me.

38:58.612 --> 39:01.697
You know,
go back to california,
excel at this job,

39:02.750 --> 39:05.083
fix up our house,
and make it a home again.

39:08.789 --> 39:10.622
Would you ever
consider moving back?

39:16.764 --> 39:18.714
My life is in st. Jo now.

39:20.100 --> 39:22.551
I have a calling,
a community here.

39:26.106 --> 39:30.976
But long weekends
in la with you
sound magnificent.

39:31.061 --> 39:32.311
They do.

39:36.567 --> 39:38.367
In the meantime,

39:38.452 --> 39:41.286
we're gonna have some bumps
in the road to smooth over

39:41.388 --> 39:42.921
for both of us.

39:44.758 --> 39:47.009
-Leave the image stuff to me.
-Yep.

39:48.095 --> 39:49.595
No time like the present,
right?

39:50.681 --> 39:51.964
Come on.

39:54.768 --> 39:56.351
[davis sighs]

39:56.437 --> 39:57.719
oh, we're doing this?

39:57.805 --> 39:59.471
-We're doing this.
